						<summary>

						<p>Ēkāmranāthasvāmin temple, north wall.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">••• ••• Year 20, 757th day, Āvaṇi.</hi></p>						

						<p>This records the perpetual grant of 500 <hi rend="italic">kuḻi</hi> of wet land and some dry cops land (2000 <hi rend="italic">kuḻi ?</hi>) out of the Vārapaṟṟu in Taḍavūr with the right to sell and mortgage, to Magadēśaṉ Ulagaṅ-kātta-Vāṇakōvaraiyaṉ Perudakāḷapparaiyaṉ Pakkam-aḻagiyāṉ. The order was attested by Siṁhaḷar[āyaṉ].</p>						

